value.value: greater count of the large, phagocytic mononuclear leukocytes produced in the vertebrate bone marrow and released into the blood
reduction in the number of nucleated cells of the myeloid or lymphoid lineages, found in blood or other tissue

deviation from normal for the average amount of space occupied by each red blood cell, calculated from the hematocrit and red cell count, in erythrocyte indices

definition.value: MCV is calculated by dividing the hematocrit by the total number of RBCs and multiplying this number by ten (10).
